This paper deals with formal proof systems and the representation of concepts in auction theory. The use of Isabelle/HOL system suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Logic in Computer Science (cs.LO) sub-category. The focus on auction theory suggests that it could also belong to the Game Theory (cs.GT) sub-category. The mention of verified code and computational content suggests that it could belong to the Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category. The discussion of set theory and higher order logic suggests that it could belong to the Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS) sub-category. Finally, the presentation of definitions and theorems suggests that it could belong to the Computational Complexity (cs.CC) sub-category.
